  "Father and son Kapil and Rahul Bhatia's (pictured) biggest asset is InterGlobe Aviation, whose IndiGo is India's biggest airline by market share.",
  "IndiGo, which was cofounded with billionaire airline veteran Rakesh Gangwal in 2006, has a 54% domestic market share. ",
  "It has a fleet of 283 aircraft and flew to 87 destinations, including 24 overseas, before the Covid-19 pandemic forced it to curtail operations.",
  "Its CEO is airline veteran Ronojoy Dutta, a former president of United Airlines.",
  "In 2019, the Bhatias and Gangwal had a public falling out over how IndiGo is run. "
